# Business Development Automation System – PromptOptimizer-Bot Scratchpad

## Multi-Agent Scratchpad

### Background and Motivation
The existing Business Development Automation System is production-ready (v1.0-google-sheets) but relies on static Jinja prompts. To improve prompt quality and reduce LLM cost, we will add **PromptOptimizer-Bot**, a MetaGPT-powered, multi-agent module that iteratively refines prompts on demand. Any bot (Outreach, Insights, Strategy, etc.) can call it via the System Coordinator.

### Key Challenges and Analysis
- MetaGPT integration and dependency management ✅ RESOLVED
- Designing agent roles (Prompt Engineer, Evaluator, Optimizer) and their interaction loop ✅ RESOLVED
- Defining automated evaluation metrics for "better" prompts ✅ RESOLVED
- Seamless hooks into existing pipelines (opt-in flag) ✅ RESOLVED
- Extending cost-tracking to MetaGPT usage ✅ RESOLVED
- Unit/integration testing with mocked LLM calls ✅ RESOLVED
- Dockerization & monitoring ✅ RESOLVED
- **NEW CHALLENGES FOR UI DASHBOARD:**
  - React/TypeScript frontend integration with existing Python FastAPI backend
  - Real-time cost data streaming and visualization
  - Grafana iframe embedding with proper authentication
  - Frontend build process integration with existing Docker/CI workflows
  - Dashboard state management for optimization runs and cost tracking
  - Security considerations for token-based authentication

### Verifiable Success Criteria
**Core Functionality (COMPLETED):**
1. ✅ `optimize_prompt()` returns an improved prompt (≥10 % fewer tokens OR higher eval score).
2. ✅ Bots can invoke optimization via CLI flag or direct call.
3. ✅ MetaGPT token/cost data appears in logs & Grafana.
4. ✅ New unit & integration tests pass in CI.
5. ✅ `docker compose up` starts a `prompt_optimizer_worker` service without errors.

**Cost-Tracking Enhancement (COMPLETED):**
6. ✅ All cost data flows correctly from API calls → CostManager → Prometheus → Grafana
7. ✅ Prometheus metrics endpoint (port 8000) exports real-time cost metrics
8. ✅ Grafana dashboard displays live cost trends and optimization statistics

**Documentation & CI (COMPLETED):**
9. ✅ Comprehensive documentation reflects all new capabilities and testing procedures
10. ✅ Developer onboarding guide covers testing framework and cost monitoring

**UI Dashboard & Control Panel (NEW):**
11. ✅ React dashboard displays recent optimization runs with cost/performance metrics
12. ✅ Grafana panels embedded via iframe show real-time cost graphs
13. ✅ Manual prompt optimization form submits and streams results to UI
14. ✅ FastAPI endpoints `/optimizer/runs` and `/optimizer/execute` return proper data
15. ✅ Dashboard authentication works with token-based system
16. ✅ Cypress tests validate UI functionality and integrate with CI pipeline
17. ✅ Conda-based local dev environment is fully functional

